**Why it exists:** DeepSeek (and other providers) don't natively throw `ContextOverflowError`. Without this bridge middleware, when token estimation undercounts and the API returns a "maximum context length" error, the deepagents SDK's built-in summarization middleware (which catches `ContextOverflowError`) never triggers, causing unrecoverable 400 errors. This middleware ensures the error propagates correctly so the SDK's safety net (emergency summarization) activates.

